==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bewhore
<hw>Be*whore"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
corrupt with regard to chastity; to make a whore of.</def> <rj><au>J.
Fletcher.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pronounce or characterize as a whore.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bewig</ent>⟦br⟧
